The jaguar in the background is the work of master ceramicist Juana Gómez Ramírez, one of the artists we support through the Escuela Nacional de Cerámica in Mexico. 

Her figures are so life-like and full of expression we can almost hear it say “Tajín on ceviche! That’s MY way to Tajín It.”​

Visit @escuelanacionaldeceramica  to learn more

latestPosts.caption:
Twist into summer mode.⛱️

Tajín Twist is the flavor your sunny days have been waiting for. 👙

Everyone has a passion project. 💫
For Tajín, it’s preserving the rich tradition of Mexican ceramic artists. 

As founding members of the National School of Ceramics, our goal is to save the rich tradition of our artisans, help them sell their work around the world, and teach the next generations of artists.

Pictured here are two traditional pieces from neighboring states Jalisco and Michoacán, along with two party classics (the guac and the margarita)

For more, visit @escuelanacionaldeceramica .
